    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The `miner` is a header-field. In the clique protocol, that header field is left blank. At one point, we did replace the header-field with the actual miner, _but_, doing so pulls the rug from ethclient: ethclient uses the header fields to reconstruct the sealhash of the block, and calculates the actual `sealer` based on that. And if we modify the header, it suddenly resolves to a different hash -> a different sealer. So we had to revert that :(\r\n\r\nSo yes, it's a bit pita. IIRC, there's another method to get the clique sealer: `clique.getSigner(hash or number or rlp)`",
